			<outline text="July 20" type="calendarDay" name="20" >
				<outline text="@FactFreeh Present for ya &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/retronewsnow/status/1417610040945565701&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 23:10:50 GMT" tweetId="1417623059679391744" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1417623059679391744" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" />
				<outline text="I’m reading these dire updates and thinking what a piece of garbage Walensky is for her incoherent advice and abrupt, unexplained reversals on masks and other safety issues. She put us all in danger and eroded public trust. Fire her, investigate her, and check the rest of the CDC &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/chrisprener/status/1417538455383511044&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 22:21:41 GMT" tweetId="1417610693088514053" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1417610693088514053" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" >
					<outline text="This absolute nut job, who went from weeping that we’re in imminent doom to saying “masks off for everyone” to “it’s a pandemic of the unvaccinated” and now has doctors around the country correcting her about risks to vaxxed, is a travesty. Ask why Biden chose her over others..." type="tweet" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 22:25:14 GMT" tweetId="1417611583367360516" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1417611583367360516" inReplyToId="1417610693088514053" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" >
						<outline text="While he’s at it, Biden should also fire Wray, Ron Bloom (in order to fire DeJoy), Garland, and I’ll just limit it to that for now. None of these people should be there. They are actively harming this country. They do not serve the American people." type="tweet" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 22:27:12 GMT" tweetId="1417612079859699720" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1417612079859699720" inReplyToId="1417611583367360516" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="FFS pay your workers and pay your taxes! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/cnn/status/1417559752779997187&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 22:03:18 GMT" tweetId="1417606065139617798" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1417606065139617798" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" />
				<outline text="Thread. Paywalls are a huge factor in covid disinfo. People don’t have the money for local, national, and science subscriptions so they learn about a pandemic through gossip and memes. My info on covid in MO comes from a local expert who pieces it together for the rest of us. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/bostonjoan/status/1417452198678630403&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 12:07:46 GMT" tweetId="1417456192922787864" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1417456192922787864" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" >
					<outline text="Publications should remove paywalls on covid stories. Otherwise people can’t keep themselves safe. Paywalls also block people from the on-the-ground reporting explaining why people actually think and behave the way they do. Local stories negate stereotypes and counteract vitriol." type="tweet" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 12:14:27 GMT" tweetId="1417457876554194944" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1417457876554194944" inReplyToId="1417456192922787864" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" >
						<outline text="Thread on paywalls and the damage to democracy. Applies to public health as well: &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1387404190390132743&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 12:21:34 GMT" tweetId="1417459665781284864" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1417459665781284864" inReplyToId="1417457876554194944" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				</outline>
